	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)">My very dear uncle&#33;&#33;&#33;</p>
				<p>Your letter and those from my dear<lb/> sisters have we all received in the<lb/> best health&#59; and hope that you may<lb/> receive this rules also in the best situation.<lb/>  Although I have read that you <sic>has</sic> been<lb/> indisposed&#59; which displeased me much&#44;<lb/> and wish you at the same time that you<lb/> are repaired again.</p>
				<p>Now <sic>me</sic> dear uncle I will also congratulate<lb/> you with your anniversary &#40;although I am<lb/> not in your presence&#41; My wish is than that<lb/> the Almighty heavenly Father preserve<lb/> you yet many years for misfortune&#59; but that<lb/> He give you a series of happy days <add>Hebrew</add>.<lb/>  I thank you also heartily that you give many a pleasure to <sic>me</sic> sisters&#59; they are very<lb/> content <sic>till</sic> here I hope it will be also in<lb/> the continuation.  I pray you to take<lb/> farther care for them&#59; be thou their father<lb/> and their conductor upon all their ways.<lb/>  We have here no winter this year&#44; it<lb/> has no fusen&#44; so that we have not skated.</p>
				<p rend="The following lines are written sideways down the left side of the page.">P. S. That the cheese is to your taste<lb/> does me a great joy&#59; eat then with a good appetite.  Farewell and think<lb/> on me.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>If my sisters send us their portraits in the<lb/> spring I beg you to send it also from you&#59;<lb/> you shall well think they have it already<lb/> from me&#59; but I would have it very willingly<lb/> for me alone&#44; I hope that you shall not fail.<lb/>  Also I pray thee to write me this time also<lb/> any rules&#44; If you cannot write a great letter<lb/> do than me the pleasure to write a little&#44;<lb/> I shall content with a few words from thee.<lb/>  Now <sic>me</sic> dear uncle <sic>life</sic> happy in the future<lb/> kiss my sisters for me&#59; and after having<lb/> saluted&#44; <del>you</del> and having kissed thee in my<lb/> thoughts I am with the most respect</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your affectionate niece till in eternity</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Jeannette Elkus</persName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">Geliebter Oheim&#33;</p>
				<p>Mit freuden ergreif ich die Faden um dich auch<lb/> Zeilen zuzuf&#252;gen&#44; und hoffe da&#223; die dieselben in den<lb/> Wohlstand er<add>&#63;</add>brief&#44; welches ich dich von meiner Seite<lb/> auf mittheilen kann&#44; Du sagt vorl&#228;ngst dein 59te<lb/> Jahr angetreten so ist meinen herzl<add>&#63;</add>sten Wunsch<lb/> da&#223; der liebe Gott dich noch viele Jahren dein<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> Leben mag <add>&#63;</add>&#44; und <add>&#63;</add> auch das<lb/> du viele Freude an meinen Mehrheiten Schonester<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> beleben&#44; nun habe wohl ge<add>&#63;</add> Onkel und<lb/> gr&#252;&#223;e dich wie<add>&#63;</add>mahl deine <add>&#63;</add><lb/> <persName role="author">Julia Elkus</persName></p>
